How to Install Angular 18 on Ubuntu
Follow the steps below to install Angular 18 on Ubuntu, based on whether or not you have Node.js installed.

If You Have Node.js Installed:
Install Angular CLI 18:
  sudo npm install -g @angular/cli@18

Create and serve a new Angular project:
  ng new my-angular-app
  cd my-angular-app
  ng serve

  

If You Don't Have Node.js Installed:
Install Node.js and npm:
  sudo apt update
  sudo apt install curl
  curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_16.x | sudo -E   -
  sudo apt install nodejs


Install Angular CLI 18:
  sudo npm install -g @angular/cli@18


Create and serve a new Angular project:
  ng new my-angular-app
  cd my-angular-app
  ng serve
